Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.15,0:00:06.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Caution... Fragile
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.61,0:00:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Chitanda, is there\Na superstition that says
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.82,0:00:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that whatever you do on New Year's Day\Nwill be repeated all year long?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't think there's\Na superstition about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, it would mean that\Nwhen you took New Year's off,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.92,0:00:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you would wind up taking\Nthe whole year off, as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which would be awfully absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I had to say, I'm more concerned\Nabout our present state
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.30,0:00:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,than I am about the other 364 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.27,0:00:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did we end up like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question. Probably because
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.48,0:00:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you picked an unlucky fortune, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.04,0:01:14.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.88,0:01:21.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.06,0:01:27.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.65,0:01:33.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.57,0:01:40.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.20,0:01:48.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.04,0:01:56.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.63,0:02:03.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:10.60,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.60,0:02:18.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.62,0:02:30.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mishap-py New Year
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chitanda.\NAm I speaking to Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.25,0:02:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.80,0:02:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, do you have any plans\Nfor New Year's Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? Well then, would\Nyou like to go visit the shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Visit the shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.06,0:02:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}said
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she was working at\NArekusu Shrine as an attendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.52,0:02:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really up her alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not very nice, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukube-{\i1}san {\i0}said that he was going, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I wondered if you would\Nlike to come, as well. Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean there's something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.66,0:03:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so much a "something," but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.62,0:03:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I kind of want to dress up in my kimono.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:18.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Arekusu Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.31,0:03:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's New Year's, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some people have gotten all dressed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.69,0:03:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.41,0:03:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy new year to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.21,0:03:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A happy new year to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:04:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to your continuing\Nfriendship in the coming year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.13,0:04:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, it is I that ask for {\i1}your {\i0}favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to show this outfit off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we get going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.98,0:04:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.49,0:04:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to carry that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.70,0:04:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. If you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bottle of saké. We have some\Ndealings with the priest here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I have come to offer\Na New Year's greeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Already running errands for\Nthe new year? What a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real hassle came during the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.55,0:04:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent the whole time paying respects\Nto relatives, and being a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, what were you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:05:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was doing my imitation of a hermit crab.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:06.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Clouds\NOdani Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.57,0:05:08.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oda Nobunaga
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:12.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagawa Yoshimoto\NMori Shinsuke
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.54,0:05:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hermit crab?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.92,0:05:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing, never mind. Where's Satoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}is the one who got\Nin touch with Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.21,0:05:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you know what, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start by offering our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.19,0:05:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May my year be spent in only\Nmoderate energy consumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy new year to you.\NOn behalf of Chitanda Tetsugo,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.92,0:06:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my name is Eru, and I have come\Nto pay my respects for the new year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm Oreki, along for the ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.67,0:06:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, please, come on in.\NI'll go get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Pardon the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is a genuine shrine\Npriestess. Very distinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy new year to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to good relations\Nwith you in the coming year, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.29,0:06:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy new year to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.17,0:06:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a bottle of saké from\Nmy father. Please accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how distinguished families\Nassociate with each other, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.68,0:07:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.02,0:07:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nothing fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, that's for me to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.82,0:07:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.90,0:07:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want it if it's not fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.36,0:07:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't say that. Please, accept\Nour gift. It is nothing fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're putting me on? And I panicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in Class B, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.67,0:07:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.25,0:07:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Fukube-{\i1}kun {\i0}was coming with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does she know that? Divine powers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Jumonji Kaho, from Class 1-B.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're classmates?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we would like to see Ibara Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara? Oh, her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.65,0:07:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This leads to the rear of\Nthe kiosks, so go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.41,0:07:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.08,0:07:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hairstyle is very becoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They put it on for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.46,0:08:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stare.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A happy new year to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy new year. That kimono\Nlooks great. It's very pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it long-sleeved?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's a normal pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.60,0:08:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will get to wear a long-sleeved\None once I go to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.97,0:08:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be done here in another hour.\NChi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.31,0:08:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I will remain in attendance\Nhere in the main hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.40,0:08:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was here during the day. He went\Nhome to watch... was it called...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dark Clouds: Odani Castle{\i0}, some drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.07,0:08:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he'll be back\Nbefore too long, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara, what are you selling there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunes. Also, I have lost-child,\Nlost-and-found, and change duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The parishioners are all worked up\Nmaking the rounds here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so if anything of even a little bit of\Nvalue gets dropped, it comes right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was busier during the day.\NLots of lost children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that anyone asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:09:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fortune would be nice. I'll take one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, pick from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that purse is terrific!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks so fancy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.11,0:09:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure seem pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:15.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, would you like to try?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! "Great Luck"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.84,0:09:32.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortune ♪10\NGreat Luck
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.34,0:09:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.34,0:09:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.38,0:09:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.52,0:09:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.81,0:09:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it's going\Nto be a great year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You drew "Good Luck\NForthcoming," didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortune ♪16\NBad Luck
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never\Nseen a "Bad Luck" fortune before today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that delighted by my "Bad Luck"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.54,0:10:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. You're right. Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nthis must be bothering you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.17,0:10:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, just give it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.75,0:10:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaho-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry, Eru. I didn't\Neven offer you any tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.68,0:10:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, never mind that,\Nhas something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the part-timers\Noverturned some pots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we have to make the dumpling soup
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sweet saké we were\Nserving all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.69,0:10:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my. Was she burned?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.10,0:10:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it sounds like she's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.98,0:10:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's okay. You can't cook\Nwhen you're dressed up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, is there anything\Nelse that I can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.82,0:10:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, could you bring in some\Nsaké lees from the storehouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're on the left right after you\Ngo in, so you'll recognize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.38,0:10:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Storehouse, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was next to the\NInari statue, as I recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:10:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoo, it's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.76,0:11:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry and get this taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not very secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.81,0:11:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope there's a light in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a wall along the left.\NCould it be further inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this would be a simple errand,\Nbut this is becoming a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, this is a shed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, call it a shed or call it\Na shack, this is the place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.38,0:11:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's the storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaho-{\i1}san {\i0}said it was in the storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.63,0:11:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! My family doesn't have a storehouse,\Nso I got mixed up! Tee-hee!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I can't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you knew that, then speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.69,0:11:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I wasn't exactly sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.69,0:11:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that the {\i1}mikoshi {\i0}storage room\Nis next to the shrine office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.07,0:12:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.70,0:12:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're locked inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:19.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Touji {\i0}('Depth of Winter')\NWhen the sun reacheth its southmost\Nextreme, and the days are shortest
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:19.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:20.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Caution... Fragile
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.93,0:12:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all because I\Nmade a stupid mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.64,0:12:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no matter what\Nkind of mistake it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.23,0:12:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we never thought that we\Nwould get locked in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll call for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.24,0:12:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to shout as loud as I can,\Nso you should cover your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, just a minute. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.49,0:12:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, just a minute. Um...\N♪ Ah... Ah... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.95,0:12:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry! But please, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.54,0:12:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, if you shout out now and call\Npeople over, what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Well, someone will probably come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll unbar the door, and open it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.22,0:13:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, how will the two of us look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How will we look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.02,0:13:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those parishioners know me.\NIf those parishioners help me out,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they're sure to misunderstand\Nwhat happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.11,0:13:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am here today representing my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were another time and place,\Nthat would be one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now, here, if they were to\Nfind me alone with you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't understand her world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. But then, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone comes here needing to\Nget something, and opens the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.63,0:13:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they're definitely going\Nto get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who would\Nunderstand our situation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are Kaho-{\i1}san {\i0}and Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.26,0:13:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:13:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:14:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple. We can use a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well sure, that would\Nwork fine. So, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.54,0:14:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't remove the door itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.83,0:14:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I forgot that\Nyou don't own a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.80,0:14:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I asked you not to\Nshout out to call anyone over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at this point, it's another story.\NLet's call someone over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't do something soon,\Nyou're going to catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're worried, aren't you?\NThat people will misunderstand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.61,0:14:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we run out of other options,\Nwe'll call for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.40,0:14:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, though, let's think\Nof anything else we can try.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.66,0:14:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't move the bar,\Nand we can't remove the hinges.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:15:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are still four avenues of\Nescape that we haven't explored.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That many?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.33,0:15:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One, we could break the door down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.34,0:15:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two, we could break the wall down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three, we could dig a hole\Nto crawl out through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four, we can open up a hole in the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we can't do those!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they {\i1}are {\i0}old, they're\Nstill Arekusu Shrine's buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess those are out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is heading this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a parishioner, making his rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he picked up\Na cell phone strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:15:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have good night vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she, a wild animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.47,0:15:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's heading back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to drop it off\Nat the shrine office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.93,0:16:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shrine office... Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Chitanda, would it be okay\Nto break open the wall a little bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.86,0:16:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ibara mentioned earlier that when\Nsomeone dropped anything of value,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.49,0:16:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the parishioners bring it\Nright to her, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And right now, Ibara is\Nin charge of lost items.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.87,0:16:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we drop something that\Nclearly belongs to us from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.71,0:16:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and have a parishioner\Ndeliver it to Ibara for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.67,0:16:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can convey our plight to her,\Nshe may come to rescue us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.67,0:16:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see what you mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How big a question it raises that\Nit was picked up near the shed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.18,0:16:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all depends on Ibara, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.93,0:16:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about my handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.77,0:16:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}has seen it many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's use that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, drop your\Nhandkerchief through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:12.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan {\i0}and Oreki are already here.\NCome to the office and wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Jumonji-{\i1}san{\i0}! Happy new year!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy new year to you.\NFukube-{\i1}kun{\i0}, have you seen Eru?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}? I just got here,\Nso I'm not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Sorry I can't show you around,\Nbut go on in on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.86,0:17:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stove is on in the great hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't know how to\Nact around Jumonji-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wah! Oh, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.33,0:17:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she still embarrassed\Nabout her attendant getup?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard work in all\Nthis cold. You're a real trouper.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.42,0:17:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-mm. But never mind me,\Nhow was your drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a masterpiece! I got to start\Nthe year with a huge smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.22,0:18:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}. Do you recognize this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to me that\NChi-{\i1}chan {\i0}had one like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.44,0:18:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice that you might know\Nwho the owner is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}gets\Nback here, you can ask her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help... isn't coming, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.87,0:18:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were headed\Nin the right direction, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.00,0:18:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess a handkerchief\Nby itself isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.21,0:18:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't something that leaves\Nmuch of an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, in that case,\Nwe move to the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.01,0:18:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try my wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.80,0:18:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.93,0:18:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.93,0:18:44.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Change made
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.97,0:18:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? Look at this, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.02,0:18:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Hotaro's wallet, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.98,0:18:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm. Looks like the idiot\Ndropped it. It's been emptied out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.06,0:18:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.23,0:18:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the fortune that he drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:18:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro went and drew "Bad Luck," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.49,0:19:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is strange.\NIt's emptier than empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.66,0:19:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me draw a fortune, too.\NThe ones here seem to really work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.87,0:19:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help isn't coming, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.09,0:19:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.80,0:19:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I wish I'd worn my haori, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haori?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a coat that you wear over a kimono.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm regretting not wearing\Na trench coat, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.39,0:19:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is getting\Na bit chilly, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Chitanda. We might not\Nbe able to hold out any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.03,0:19:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's reached Ibara by now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it wasn't enough to make her\Nskip out of work and come look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. Thanks for going along\Nwith my selfish request for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.41,0:19:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't being selfish;\Nit's your responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't excuse dragging\Nyou along with me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.42,0:19:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call for help. There's no getting\Naround some degree of gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukube-{\i1}san {\i0}should be\Nhere by now, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.68,0:20:12.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Bowls
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.89,0:20:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, do you have any kind of string?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-String, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.73,0:20:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About this much. 50 cm long\Nshould be plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we have that, I can definitely\Nlet Satoshi know of our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The strap from my sandals?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too short.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I have the drawstring from my purse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.50,0:20:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't work. We're going\Nto use your purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, what about your shoelace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.33,0:20:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm wearing boots today, with no laces.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's no other choice, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we might be able\Nto use my sash's {\i1}obijime{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.26,0:20:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a string?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.60,0:20:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.64,0:20:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will taking it off be hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, well, I suppose.\NIt will take a little effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Chitanda, I don't know\Nmuch about kimonos,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.15,0:21:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you remove the {\i1}obijime{\i0},\Nwill the kimono still be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.70,0:21:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sash will pretty much fall down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's not an option, is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.62,0:21:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some other string\Naround anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how will you be able to get help\Nfrom Fukube-{\i1}san {\i0}with a string?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.59,0:21:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember there being\Na flag outside the shed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.01,0:21:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.36,0:21:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've found a string!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.82,0:21:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, let me have your purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.20,0:21:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.12,0:21:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is definitely Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s\Npurse! I saw it earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.79,0:22:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A handkerchief, a wallet,\Nand now a purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if this is Hotaro's\N"Bad Luck" at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said they found this\Nnext to the shed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what the two\Nof them could be doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.39,0:22:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a dirty old string\Nattached to it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,String?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.77,0:22:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.90,0:22:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's the matter, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.19,0:22:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, where's the shed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.44,0:22:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over that way. Next to the Inari statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.03,0:22:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.99,0:22:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},\NI'm coming to save you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.12,0:22:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your purse is a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.92,0:22:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you tie up the\Nopening and the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.67,0:22:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it closes up whatever is inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.84,0:22:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like in the expression\N"trapped like a rat in a bag."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.88,0:22:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A rat in a bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.93,0:22:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the one who thought it up.\NIt comes from a historic episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.85,0:22:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of the\NBattle of Anegawa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.22,0:22:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a famous story that came\Nbefore it; do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.56,0:23:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The withdrawal from Kanegazaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.56,0:23:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Nobunaga was laying\Nsiege to the Asakura Clan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobunaga's brother-in-law,\NAzai, betrayed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.44,0:23:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobunaga's sister, Lady Oichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.82,0:23:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sent a bean bag tied up at both\Nends to Nobunaga in the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.33,0:23:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to convey to him that she\Nwas a "rat in a bag."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.37,0:23:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know how much\Nof it is actually true, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.08,0:23:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's such a tale, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.79,0:23:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just today, both Satoshi and I saw\Nthat episode play out in a drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing him, he'll\Nunderstand what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.60,0:23:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro! Are you in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.60,0:23:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved us. We were\Nabout to freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.73,0:23:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're serving hot\Nsweet saké at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll open the door now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.49,0:23:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.16,0:23:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mis-happy new year!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.66,0:23:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.83,0:23:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mis-happy new year.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.22,0:24:26.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.90,0:24:29.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.57,0:24:35.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.53,0:24:37.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.79,0:24:43.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:48.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.38,0:24:55.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.18,0:24:59.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.85,0:25:05.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.44,0:25:10.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.15,0:25:17.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.70,0:25:23.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.37,0:25:30.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.34,0:25:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Case of\Nthe Homemade Chocolates."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.60,0:25:43.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the Homemade Chocolates
